(ooc: Element split up into seperate bots, kslawdoggie :)


+++Cledar Rixer Truttle Forrior Blyer Mantle+++

Rixer's two bee-bots managed to destroy every missile heading toward the 
Cybertronian Fire except for one of Firestarter's, which ended up hitting. 
They also destroyed two missiles heading for Zardus, one that was heading 
for Rixer, and one that was heading for Darkfate.



Rixer watched a missile come close but then be destroyed by one of his bee 
bots. He smiled and aimed his missile launcher. Rixer fired two seeking 
missiles at Reflector and then twenty plasma shots at him. This battle was a 
breathe so far.


Blyer saw a jet flying by behind him, and his scanners told him that the jet 
was Firestarter. He lowered altitude, eager to shot this Pred who's boss, 
and fired two missiles down at him. He then aimed his machine gun and fired 
twenty laser shots.


Seeing that Hell Beast wasn't at the battle anymore, Truttle turned his 
attention to Injector. He fired twenty shots from each machine gun at him.


Forrior watched his shots hit and smiled. His cannon fired another plasma 
shot at Predator, but this one was aimed down toward the ground. It made a 
huge explosion when it hit and would hopefully envelop Predator in it.



Mantle entered the Element and looked around. A screen lowered in front of 
him with a boyish face of a bot on it.

"Hello Mantle!" Cyndro's voice sounded from the panel. "How's the battle?"

"Pretty good, Cyndro." replied Mantle. "We might have use for your nano bots 
soon, Cyndro. Can you prepare them."

"Sure can!" The panel folded back into the roof and Mantle turned around to 
wait for Epyon.
